special_powers.name: WILL: BEST OF THE BEST

special_powers.name: THIS IS MY PERSONAL SPACE - BACK OFF!
special_powers.description: Hal Jordan and Sinestro can use Running Shot. When they do, they can use the Duo Attack ability instead of a ranged combat action, but the second attack can't target the same character as the first attack.

special_powers.name: ONLY LIMITED BY YOUR IMAGINATION
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, Hal Jordan and Sinestro may choose a standard attack power they didn't choose during their last turn and use that power until your next turn.

special_powers.name: RESTORE THE GREEN
special_powers.description: Give Swamp Thing a move action, after actions resolve, you may place hindering terrain markers in any clear squares he moved through and he may make a close combat attack targeting one opposing character occupying a hindering terrain marker Swamp Thing just placed. These markers aren't removed when Swamp Thing is KO'd.

special_powers.name: FOUR ELEMENTS JOINED
special_powers.description: Once during your turn, you may choose one: Air, Earth, Fire, or Water. Swamp Thing can use the associated power until you choose again. Air - Telekinesis; Earth - Barrier; Fire - Energy Explosion; Water - Shape Change.

special_powers.name: LIFE
special_powers.description: Swamp Thing can use Regeneration. When turning the dial, if this click is revealed due to damage taken from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: RESURRECT THE FALLEN
special_powers.description: When a friendly character within range and occupying hindering terrain would be KO'd, roll a d6. On a result of 5, instead click them to their last non-KO click, heal them 1 click, and they are now assigned 1 action token. On a result of 6, instead click them to their last non-KO click, heal them 2 clicks, and remove all action tokens they are assigned.

special_powers.name: CRYPTKEEPER OF THE CORPS
special_powers.description: When another friendly character with the Green Lantern Corps keyword is KO'd, turn it to any click and then place it on this card. Morro can use any standard powers on that click.

special_powers.name: WILL: RELENTLESS
special_powers.description: Morro can use Willpower. When an opposing character targets Morro with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6, ignore that effect. When an opposing character within 6 squares takes pushing damage, heal Morro 1 click.

special_powers.name: WHAT ARE YOU TRULY AFRAID OF?
special_powers.description: If an opponent wins the roll to determine the first player and does not choose Parallax's controller to be the first player, characters on that opponent's force modify their attack value by -1 as long as Parallax is on the map.

special_powers.name: IN THE GRIP OF FEAR
special_powers.description: Parallax can use Charge and Plasticity.

special_powers.name: FEAR: DESPAIR
special_powers.description: Parallax can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values. When he does, decrease the same combat value on all other opposing characters within his range and line of fire.

special_powers.name: SEEK FORGIVENESS FOR YOUR SINS
special_powers.description: When a friendly character takes damage from an attack, after actions resolve, give the attacking character an action token.

special_powers.name: COMPASSION: REDEMPTION
special_powers.description: When a non-adjacent friendly character within 6 squares takes 3 or more damage, after actions resolve, if that character hasn't been healed this turn, you may place Sinestro adjacent to that character and heal that character of 1 damage. That character can't be attacked again this turn even if this power is lost.

special_powers.name: DON'T YOU GET IT? I'M STRONGER THAN YOU!
special_powers.description: When Superboy Prime is dealt penetrating damage from a character of 150 points or less, it can be reduced.

special_powers.name: RUN, COWARDS!
special_powers.description: Superboy Prime's attacks generate knockback and opposing characters that take damage from his attacks are given an action token.

special_powers.name: FEAR SUBMISSION
special_powers.description: Superboy Prime can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values. When he does, decrease the chosen combat value by an additional amount equal to the number of action tokens on the target at this time.

special_powers.name: RAGE OF A PETULANT CHILD
special_powers.description: Superboy Prime can use Poison and deals penetrating damage while using it. Opposing characters can't counter Superboy Prime's other powers and abilities or modify his combat values.

special_powers.name: DAYBREAK
special_powers.description: Superboy Prime can use Regeneration and Toughness. When he occupies outdoor terrain and uses Regeneration, don't subtract 2 from the d6 roll.

special_powers.name: DEATH: ENCOMPASSING
special_powers.description: Galius Zed can use Steal Energy. When an opposing character is KO'd, heal Galius Zed of 1 damage. Galius Zed begins the game on click #3 and can use this trait to heal past its starting click.

special_powers.name: DESPAIR OF THE GREEN LANTERNS
special_powers.description: When an opposing character rolls for Leadership, Shape Change, or Super Senses, and the result is 1 - 4, modify Galius Zed's combat values by +1 until the end of your next turn. If that character has the Green Lantern Corps keyword, modify that character's combat values by -1 until your next turn.

special_powers.name: CONSTRICTING BITE
special_powers.description: Ziilus Zox can use Blades/Claws/Fangs and Plasticity. When he rolls a d6 for Blades/Claws/Fangs, put a number of Bite tokens on this card equal to his printed damage value minus the result of the d6 roll (minimum 0). Give Zilius Zox a free action and remove two Bite tokens to make a close combat attack as a free action.

special_powers.name: RAGE
special_powers.description: Zilius Zox can use Poison and deals penetrating damage when using it.

special_powers.name: ATTACKS ROLL OFF ME
special_powers.description: Zilius Zox can use Shape Change and Toughness.

special_powers.name: CONSTRUCT
special_powers.description: When building your force, you may attach a construct to this character by paying its point cost. Give this character a power action and replace the construct with any other construct, up to 2 points higher than the original construct. If this character has no action tokens and the new construct is a lower point value than the original construct, this is a free action instead.

special_powers.name: VOLUNTEER TO BE FIRST INTO BATTLE
special_powers.description: Galius Zed can use Sidestep. If Galius Zed is the friendly character farthest from your starting area, modify his speed and attack values by +1. When Galius Zed makes a close combat attack, it generates knockback.

special_powers.name: WILL
special_powers.description: Galius Zed can use Willpower. When an opposing character targets Galius Zed with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6 ignore that effect.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Black Hand is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the Black Lantern Corps keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: OBLIVION OF DEATH
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the Black Lantern Corps keyword is healed because an opposing character is KO'd, increase the healing by 1.

special_powers.name: DEATH
special_powers.description: Black Hand can use Steal Energy. When an opposing character is KO'd, heal Black Hand of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: DESPAIR OF THE BLACKEST NIGHT
special_powers.description: When an opposing chararacter misses an attack, choose an opposing character within 10 squares and line of fire and modify that character's defense value by -1 until the end of your next turn.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Entity is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the White Lantern Corps keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: FLOW OF LIFE
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, you may heal one adjacent character without the Black Lantern Corps keyword 1 click.

special_powers.name: COSMIC LIFE
special_powers.description: Entity can use Regeneration and the Quintessence team ability. When turning the dial, if this click is revealed due to damage taken from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Ion is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the Green Lantern Corps keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose up to 2 different powers on the equipped dial and up to 2 different combat values on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use those powers and modifies those combat values by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: FORCE OF WILL
special_powers.description: Friendly characters can use Willpower. If they can already do so, increase their defense value by the number of action tokens on them.

special_powers.name: COSMIC WILL
special_powers.description: Ion can use the Quintessence team ability. When an opposing character targets Ion with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6, ignore that effect.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Ophidian is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the Orange Lantern Corps keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: COSMIC GREED
special_powers.description: Ophidian can use Barrier, Plasticity, and the Quintessence team ability.

special_powers.name: DESIRE OF GREED
special_powers.description: Ophidian can use Outwit. When it does it can use the countered power or ability for as long as it's countered.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Proselyte is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the Indigo Tribe keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: CHANNEL THE LIGHT OF THE OTHER CORPS
special_powers.description: Give Proselyte a free action and choose a color that isn't brown, black, grey or pink.  Proselyte can use a standard power of the chosen color until your next turn.

special_powers.name: COSMIC COMPASSION
special_powers.description: When an non-adjacent friendly character within 6 squares takes 3 or more damage, after actions resolve, if that figure hasn't been healed this turn, you may place Proselyte adjacent to that figure and heal that figure of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: HEART OF COMPASSION
special_powers.description: Friendly figures that can use Support may do so even if an opposing figure is adjacent to the friendly figure or the target.  When they do modify the result of the 2d6 roll by +2 and don't subtract 2 from the d6 roll.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Parallax is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. special_powers.name: GRIP OF FEAR
special_powers.description: Opposing characters can't ignore pushing damage.

special_powers.name: COSMIC FEAR
special_powers.description: Parallax can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values. Parallax can use the Quintessence team ability.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION

special_powers.name: COSMIC RAGE
special_powers.description: Butcher can use Poison, and deals penetrating damage when using it. Butcher can use the Quintessence team ability.

special_powers.name: BLADES OF THE BUTCHER
special_powers.description: Butcher can use Blades/Claws/Fangs. When he does, add 2 to the result.

special_powers.name: HEAT OF RAGE
special_powers.description: Once per turn, a friendly character may reroll the d6 roll for Blades/Claws/Fangs.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION

This character has the Blue Lantern Corps keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: SURGE OF HOPE
special_powers.description: Friendly characters who can use Empower or Enhancement treat other friendly characters within 3 squares and line of fire of that character as adjacent for the purposes of those powers.

special_powers.name: COSMIC HOPE
special_powers.description: Adara can use Perplex, but only to increase combat values. Adara can use the Quintessence team ability.

special_powers.name: ENTITY POSSESSION
special_powers.description: When Predator is KO'd or if you pay 25 points when building your force, equip this character to a friendly character and link it to that character's dial.   This character has the Star Sapphires keyword. At the beginning of your turn or after this character is clicked, you may choose 1 power on the equipped dial and 1 combat value on the equipped dial higher than this character's same printed combat value. This character can use that power and modifies that combat value by +1 until your next turn or clicked.

special_powers.name: COSMIC LOVE
special_powers.description: Predator can use Shape Change, the Quintessence and Mystics team ability.

special_powers.name: POWER OF LOVE
special_powers.description: All characters within range can use Mind Control.

special_powers.name: VIRUS
special_powers.description: Despotellis does not require opponents to break away. Despotellis does not block line of fire and cannot have its combat values increased.

special_powers.name: THE SICKNESS IS ALREADY INSIDE YOU
special_powers.description: When an adjacent opposing character is moved or placed, you may place Despotellis adjacent to that character after the actions resolve. When an adjacent opposing character is KO'd, you may place Despotellis adjacent to another opposing character after actions resolve.

special_powers.name: PANDEMIC OF FEAR
special_powers.description: Despotellis can use Poison. When he does, he may use it normally, or instead deal each adjacent opposing character penetrating damage equal to the number of action tokens on that character. This power cannot be countered.

special_powers.name: FEAR: MASTER
special_powers.description: Sinestro can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values. When he does, he modifies all combat values on the target by -1, or all by -2 if the target has two action tokens.

special_powers.name: YOUR FEAR BETRAYS YOU
special_powers.description: Sinestro can use Sidestep. Give Sinestro a power action and place him adjacent to an opposing character with 2 action tokens.

special_powers.name: I SMELL YOUR FEAR
special_powers.description: When Sinestro attacks a character that has a combat value reduced below its printed value, he deals penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: CONSTRUCT
special_powers.description: When building your force, you may attach a construct (Lantern) to this character by paying its point cost. Give this character a power action and replace the construct with any other construct, up to 2 points higher than the original construct. If this character has no action tokens and the new construct is a lower point value than the original construct, this is a free action instead.

special_powers.name: POWER RING MASTERY
special_powers.description: Hal Jordan can use Telekinesis as a free action, if he has no action tokens.

special_powers.name: WILL: LIMITLESS RESERVE
special_powers.description: Hal Jordan can use Willpower, and opposing characters can't use Perplex to modify his combat values. When a second action token is placed on Hal Jordan, roll a d6. On a result of 3-6, heal Hal Jordan of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: TIME CUBE
special_powers.description: Once per game when Rond Vidar is hit with an attack, you may place him or the attacker in their respective starting area.

special_powers.name: UNDERCOVER GREEN LANTERN
special_powers.description: Rond Vidar can use Shape Change and Stealth.

special_powers.name: WILL
special_powers.description: Rond Vidar can use Willpower. When an opposing character targets Rond Vidar with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6 ignore that effect.

special_powers.name: I'M NOT YOUR MULE, FUZZY BLUE ELF!
special_powers.description: During your first turn, Guy Gardner can use the Carry ability to carry up to 8 characters, regardless of their combat symbols.

special_powers.name: GET IN YOUR FACE
special_powers.description: Guy Gardner can use Charge. Give Guy Gardner a move action, and if he ends his move adjacent to an opposing character, the move action counts as a free action instead, and he uses Battle Fury until that character is KO'd.

special_powers.name: WILL
special_powers.description: Guy Gardner can use Willpower. When an opposing character targets Guy Gardner with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6 ignore that effect.

special_powers.description: When building your force, you may attach a construct to this character by paying its point cost. special_powers.name: MILITARY TRAINING

special_powers.description: When building your force, you may attach a construct (Lantern) to this character by paying its point cost. If this character has no action tokens and the new construct is a lower point value than the original construct, this is a free action instead.

special_powers.name: MY FAMILY LEGACY
special_powers.description: When Jade targets a character in hindering terrain with an attack, Jade modifies her attack value by +1 and the target can't use Stealth this turn.

special_powers.name: WILL
special_powers.description: Jade can use Willpower. When an opposing character targets Jade with Outwit or Perplex, roll a d6, and on a result of 4-6 ignore that effect.

special_powers.name: I CAN BE EVERYWHERE I NEED TO BE
special_powers.description: Kyle Rayner can use the Duo Attack Ability. When he does, before making each attack, you may place him in a legal square up to half his speed value away.

special_powers.name: ION
special_powers.description: When this click is revealed due to an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. Kyle Rayner can use Impervious and the Quintessence team ability. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: RETURN FROM THE REALM OF THE DEAD
special_powers.description: Once per game, when Simon Baz would be KO'd, click him to click 4 instead.

special_powers.name: WILL: COURAGE
special_powers.description: Simon Baz can use Willpower. Opposing characters that can use Exploit Weakness or Penetrating/Psychic Blast roll a d6 before attempting to draw a line of fire to Simon Baz. On a result of 4-6, they can't draw a line of fire to him.

special_powers.name: CONSTRUCT ABSORPTION
special_powers.description: Opposing characters that can use Barrier or have a (Lantern Symbol) or (Ring Symbol) attached to them or on their card modify their combat values by -1.

special_powers.name: GREED: BARRICADING
special_powers.description: Larfleeze can use Barrier and Plasticity. When Larfleeze uses Barrier, after actions resolve, he can use Quake as a free action as if he occupied all blocking terrain markers placed by friendly characters with the Orange Lantern Corps keyword.

special_powers.name: SUMMON THE ORANGE LANTERN CORPS
special_powers.description: Give Larfleeze a free action to place a WOL #H001 Orange Lantern Absorbed into an adjacent square. Give Larfleeze a power action to place a WOL #001 Orange Lantern Construct into an adjacent square. Use these abilities only if no more than 3 total friendly characters, including tokens within stacks, with either name are on the map.

special_powers.name: BRAWLER
special_powers.description: Arkillo can use Charge and Flurry.

special_powers.name: WHIP THEM INTO SHAPE, LITERALLY

special_powers.name: FEAR: SPREADING
special_powers.description: Arkillo can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values. When a friendly character with the Sinestro Corps keyword uses Perplex, modify its range value by +3.

special_powers.name: HOPE PULLS US THROUGH THE WORST OF TIMES
special_powers.description: Saint Walker can use Probability Control. Once per turn, when a friendly character with the Blue Lantern Corps keyword uses Probability Control and the reroll is a critical miss or critical hit, you may have that roll be rerolled again.

special_powers.name: HOPE: RISING
special_powers.description: Saint Walker can use Perplex, but only to increase combat values. When a friendly character with the Blue Lantern Corps keyword uses Perplex, modify its range value by +3.

special_powers.name: RAGE: BUILDING
special_powers.description: Atrocitus can use Poison and deals penetrating damage when using it. Friendly characters with the Red Lantern Corps keyword that use Poison can use it to deal 2 damage instead of 1 if they are adjacent to two opposing characters or fewer.

special_powers.name: BLOOD PROPHECY

special_powers.name: COMPASSION: DEFENDING

special_powers.name: LOVE: THE GRANDEST EMOTION
special_powers.description: Star Sapphire can use Shape Change and the Mystics team ability. When a friendly character with the Star Sapphires keyword uses the Mystics team ability, give the attacker an action token.

special_powers.name: HAL'S WINGMAN

special_powers.name: MECHANIC OF FERRIS AIR

special_powers.name: MINIONS, HOLD HIM

special_powers.name: HORDE: NEW FLESH TO SERVE NEKRON

special_powers.name: HORDE: WAVE OF FEAR
special_powers.description: Yellow Lantern Initiate can use Pulse Wave. Unless it is M, this use of Pulse Wave ignores characters with no action tokens.

special_powers.name: HORDE: CORPS BACKUP
special_powers.description: When M, Green Lantern Initiate can use Running Shot and has "2 Bolts".

WILL:. If this character already has the Green Lantern Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Green Lantern Corps keyword, can use Willpower, and when an opposing character targets it with Outwit or Perplex, roll a D6. On a result of 4-6, ignore that effect.

LIFE:. If this character already has the White Lantern Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the White Lantern Corps keyword and once per game, when this character would be KO'd, instead turn to its last non-KO click and it can use Regeneration during your next turn.

RAGE:. If this character already has the Red Lantern Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Red Lantern Corps keyword, can use Poison, and deals penetrating damage when using it.

GREED:. If this character already has the Orange Lantern keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Orange Lantern keyword, and can use Barrier and Plasticity.

COMPASSION:. If this character already has the Indigo Tribe keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Indigo Tribe keyword, can use Support, and when a non-adjacent friendly character within 6 squares takes 3 or more damage, after actions resolve, if that character hasn't been healed this turn, you may place this character adjacent to that character and heal that character of 1 damage.

FEAR:. If this character already has the Sinestro Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Sinestro Corps keyword and can use Perplex, but only to decrease combat values.

LOVE:. If this character already has the Star Sapphires keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Star Sapphires keyword, the Mystics team ability, and can use Shape Change.

HOPE:. If this character already has the Blue Lantern Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Blue Lantern Corps keyword and can use Perplex, but only to increase combat values.

DEATH:. If this character already has the Black Lantern Corps keyword, modify all of its combat values except damage by +1. Otherwise, this character has the Black Lantern Corps keyword, can use Steal Energy, and when an opposing character is KO'd, heal this character of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: Power Battery
special_powers.description: Orange squares are Power Battery squares. The player who chose this map may choose to place a WOL #R100 Power Battery (Green Lantern Corps) that is already part of his or her force in the Power Battery squares, but only if its Emotional Spectrum trait is active. Once a Power Battery has been placed, no other player may place one. At the end of the Power Battery player's turn, roll a d6 and on a result of 5-6, you may remove 1 action token from a friendly Corps Member that currently has 2. NOT FOR TOURNAMENT PLAY.

special_powers.name: Plasma Pillars
special_powers.description: Orange squares are Plasma Pillar squares. During the beginning of your turn, any hindering or blocking terrain markers in Plasma Pillar squares are removed from the game and any character occupying a Plasma Pillar square is dealt 1 unavoidable damage for each action token they are currently assigned.

special_powers.name: Power Battery

Once a Power Battery has been placed, no other player may place one. When a Corps Member friendly to the Power Battery uses Barrier, it may place up to an additional 2 blocking terrain markers. NOT FOR TOURNAMENT PLAY.

After actions resolve, if a character who can't use the Flight ability occupies an Open Air square, deal them 1 unavoidable damage, then that character's owner places them in their starting area. Non-held objects in Open Air squares are removed from the map.

Once a Power Battery has been placed, no other player may place one. When a Corps Member friendly to the Power Battery uses Support, add 1 to the amount healed. NOT FOR TOURNAMENT PLAY.
